# How can you pick a random item from a range?


'''Python has an in-built module called 'random' which is used 
to generate random values using its methods.

We can use its method .randrange() and then pass any range as parameters.
Here's an example:-'''

import random as r
print(r.randrange(1,10))

'''this will fetch any random value between 1 and 10(excluded) and print it.

Or we can have a list of our range and then use loop to traverse through it
and use random.choice() to pick random value every time.

Here's an example:-'''

names=['Shivam','Vyom','Aastha','Nandini']
for i in range(1):
    print(r.choice(names))